ulmonary syndrome after auxiliary partial orthotopic liver transplantation in Abernethy malformation: a case report. <em>Liver Transpl</em> 2007;13(12):1662–1668.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/lt.21349">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/18044784/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Resolution+of+hepatopulmonary+syndrome+after+auxiliary+partial+orthotopic+liver+transplantation+in+Abernethy+malformation%3A+a+case+report&amp;author=S+Emre&amp;author=R+Arnon&amp;author=E+Cohen&amp;author=RA+Morotti&amp;author=D+Vaysman&amp;author=BL+Shneider&amp;publication_year=2007&amp;journal=Liver+Transpl&amp;pages=1662-1668&amp;doi=10.1002%2Flt.21349&amp;pmid=18044784">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">42.</div><div id="r42" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Konstas AA, Digumarthy SR, Avery LL, et al. Congenital portosystemic shunts: imaging findings and clinical presentations in 11 patients. <em>Eur J Radiol</em> 2010 Jan 25. [Epub ahead of print]</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/20106622/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Congenital+portosystemic+shunts%3A+imaging+findings+and+clinical+presentations+in+11+patients&amp;author=AA+Konstas&amp;author=SR+Digumarthy&amp;author=LL+Avery&amp;publication_year=2010+Jan+25&amp;journal=Eur+J+Radiol&amp;pmid=20106622">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">43.</div><div id="r43" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Schettino GC, Fagundes ED, Roquete ML, Ferreira AR, Penna FJ. Portal vein thrombosis in children and adolescents. <em>J Pediatr (Rio J)</em> 2006;82(3): 171–178.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16773174/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Portal+vein+thrombosis+in+children+and+adolescents&amp;author=GC+Schettino&amp;author=ED+Fagundes&amp;author=ML+Roquete&amp;author=AR+Ferreira&amp;author=FJ+Penna&amp;publication_year=2006&amp;journal=J+Pediatr+%28Rio+J%29&amp;pages=171-178&amp;pmid=16773174">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">44.</div><div id="r44" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Gallego C, Miralles M, Marín C, Muyor P, González G, García-Hidalgo E. Congenital hepatic shunts. <em>RadioGraphics</em> 2004;24(3):755–772.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.243035046">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15143226/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Congenital+hepatic+shunts&amp;author=C+Gallego&amp;author=M+Miralles&amp;author=C+Mar%C3%ADn&amp;author=P+Muyor&amp;author=G+Gonz%C3%A1lez&amp;author=E+Garc%C3%ADa-Hidalgo&amp;publication_year=2004&amp;journal=RadioGraphics&amp;pages=755-772&amp;doi=10.1148%2Frg.243035046&amp;pmid=15143226">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">45.</div><div id="r45" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Takeichi T, Okajima H, Suda H, et al. Living domino liver transplantation in an adult with congenital absence of portal vein. <em>Liver Transpl</em> 2005;11(10): 1285–1288.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1002/lt.20561">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16184557/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Living+domino+liver+transplantation+in+an+adult+with+congenital+absence+of+portal+vein&amp;author=T+Takeichi&amp;author=H+Okajima&amp;author=H+Suda&amp;publication_year=2005&amp;journal=Liver+Transpl&amp;pages=1285-1288&amp;doi=10.1002%2Flt.20561&amp;pmid=16184557">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">46.</div><div id="r46" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Matsubara T, Sumazaki R, Saitoh H, Imai H, Nakayama J, Takita H. Patent ductus venosus associated with tumor-like lesions of the liver in a young girl. <em>J Pediatr Gastroenterol Nutr</em> 1996;22(1): 107–111.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1097/00005176-199601000-00018">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/8788297/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Patent+ductus+venosus+associated+with+tumor-like+lesions+of+the+liver+in+a+young+girl&amp;author=T+Matsubara&amp;author=R+Sumazaki&amp;author=H+Saitoh&amp;author=H+Imai&amp;author=J+Nakayama&amp;author=H+Takita&amp;publication_year=1996&amp;journal=J+Pediatr+Gastroenterol+Nutr&amp;pages=107-111&amp;doi=10.1097%2F00005176-199601000-00018&amp;pmid=8788297">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div><div role="listitem" data-has="label"><div class="label">47.</div><div id="r47" class="citations"><div class="citation"><div class="citation-content">Dachman AH, Pakter RL, Ros PR, Fishman EK, Goodman ZD, Lichtenstein JE. Hepatoblastoma: radiologic-pathologic correlation in 50 cases. <em>Radiology</em> 1987;164(1):15–19.</div><div class="external-links"><div cl